title: 107_hr2619
content: GabrielenoTongva Nation Act - Reaffirms Federal recognition of the GabrielenoTongva Nation. Entitles such Nation to the Federal services and benefits provided to recognized Indians and restores all member rights and privileges which may have been abrogated or diminished before this Act's enactment. Provides for lands to be acquired and held in trust for the Nation by the Secretary of the Interior.
